@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

left to right direction
title FIG-12-04. Horizon Bank Payment Threat-Model DFD

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F7F9FB
}
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}
skinparam database {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F2F5F7
}
skinparam queue {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F2F5F7
}

rectangle "Retail\nCustomer" as Customer
rectangle "Operations\nAnalyst" as Ops
rectangle "Compliance\nOfficer" as Compliance
rectangle "Approved Event\nConsumer" as EventConsumer

rectangle "Digital Channel Access Context" as DigitalChannelContext {
  rectangle "boundary basis:\ninternet-facing session termination\nand channel access controls" as DigitalChannelBasis
  component "Horizon Digital\nChannels" as Channels
}

rectangle "Payment Platform Responsibility" as PaymentContext {
  rectangle "boundary basis:\npayment orchestration policy" as PaymentBasis
  component "Authorised Operations\nInterface" as OpsInterface
  component "Payments\nPlatform" as Payments
  database "Payment\nRecord Store" as PaymentStore
  database "Audit Log" as AuditLog
}

rectangle "Financial-Crime Responsibility" as FinancialCrimeContext {
  rectangle "boundary basis:\npolicy authority" as FinancialCrimeBasis
  component "Financial Crime\nPlatform" as FinancialCrime
}

rectangle "Retained Core Responsibility" as CoreContext {
  rectangle "boundary basis:\ncore account posting" as CoreBasis
  database "Core Deposit\nSystem" as Core
}

rectangle "Event Distribution Context" as EventContext {
  rectangle "boundary basis:\nevent governance and\nconsumer access" as EventBasis
  queue "Event Platform" as EventPlatform
}

Customer --> Channels : payment instruction\nand session reference\n[T12-01]
Channels --> Payments : payment instruction,\nvalidated subject context\nand entitlement context\n[T12-02, T12-07]

Payments --> FinancialCrime : screening request
FinancialCrime --> Payments : screening result\n[T12-05]
FinancialCrime --> Compliance : screening case and permitted\ncustomer context
Compliance --> FinancialCrime : screening case action\n[T12-05]

Payments --> OpsInterface : repair work item and permitted\npayment context
OpsInterface --> Ops : assigned repair case and permitted\npayment context
Ops --> OpsInterface : controlled repair action through\nauthorised operations interface\n[T12-04, T12-08]
OpsInterface --> Payments : authorised repair request

Payments --> Core : posting request\n[T12-03]
Core --> Payments : posting result

Payments --> PaymentStore : store payment record
Payments --> AuditLog : write audit event\n[T12-04]
Payments --> EventPlatform : payment-status event\n[T12-06]
EventPlatform --> EventConsumer : permitted payment-status event

legend bottom
Threat IDs label review points, not proof of vulnerability.
Authentication and session validation are represented in the authentication model, not as a full Identity Service flow here.
DFD elements are external entities, processes, stores and data flows, not BPMN process steps.
endlegend
@enduml
